VALUES ('eb4d4fb7-1c3a-4652-bd6e-cc7776062c64', 'Which choice most logically completes the text?', 'A chemist tested a newly synthesized catalyst by running the same reaction at five temperatures. At each temperature, the reaction proceeded faster with the catalyst present than without it. The chemist noticed, however, that the speed advantage provided by the catalyst shrank steadily as the temperature rose, until at the highest temperature tested the catalyzed and uncatalyzed reactions finished almost simultaneously. No other conditions—pressure, reactant concentration, or vessel size—varied across the trials. If this trend were to continue beyond the tested range, it would follow that at sufficiently high temperatures the catalyst ______', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"would offer little or no advantage in reaction speed.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: the advantage shrinks as temperature rises and nearly vanishes at the highest tested point, so extending the trend yields negligible benefit."},{"id":"B","text":"would slow the reaction below its uncatalyzed rate.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"No evidence: the trend approaches equality, not a reversal in which the catalyst slows the reaction."},{"id":"C","text":"would permanently lose its chemical structure.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"No evidence: nothing in the text concerns the catalyst''s structural stability."},{"id":"D","text":"would become more effective than at lower temperatures.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Reverse: the advantage decreases with temperature, so effectiveness would not increase."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Track the shrinking advantage
The text states the speed advantage {{yellow:shrank steadily as the temperature rose, until at the highest temperature tested the catalyzed and uncatalyzed reactions finished almost simultaneously}}.
Step 2 — Extend the trend
Continuing this decline beyond the tested range means the catalyst''s benefit becomes little or none at sufficiently high temperatures.
Distractor analysis:
- B: No evidence the trend reverses into slowing; it only approaches equality.
- C: No evidence about the catalyst losing its structure.
- D: Reverses the observed direction of the trend.', 'Extrapolate the shrinking gap—what happens to the advantage as it keeps shrinking?', 'Information and Ideas', 'Inferences', 'reading_writing', 'information', 'INF', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
